    {
      "date_stolen": 1752285600,
      "description": "Color: Dark blue frame with a glossy finish. The paint shows minor scuffs and wear, particularly near the bottom bracket and chainstay, reflecting typical usage.\r\n\r\nFrame Size & Design: The bike features a medium-sized frame with a slightly slanted top tube. The tube joints are visibly welded and reinforced, providing extra durability for off-road or urban riding.\r\n\r\nGears & Drivetrain: Equipped with a standard multi-speed gear setup. It has a triple chainring in the front and a 7-speed cassette in the rear, allowing for smooth shifting over a range of terrains. The derailleurs and shifters are operational but show minor signs of use.\r\n\r\nBrakes: The bike uses traditional rim brakes, both front and rear, which are in good working order. The brake levers on the handlebars are black and slightly worn from use.\r\n\r\nHandlebars: The handlebars are flat, straight, and black, with wear visible on the grips. The right grip end has a small cap missing, exposing the inner handlebar tube. The handlebar stem shows slight rust and wear, while the cables for the brakes and shifters are externally routed, curving smoothly toward the frame.\r\n\r\nTires & Wheels: The tires are thick, knobby, and designed for multi-surface riding, with a deep tread pattern ideal for gravel or rough urban surfaces. The tires are mounted on aluminum rims, which appear to be in good shape. Both wheels are secured with standard quick-release mechanisms.\r\n\r\nSaddle: The saddle is a basic black vinyl model, showing slight wear but no visible damage. It's supported by a standard seat post with a quick-release mechanism for easy height adjustments.\r\n\r\nWater Bottle & Holder: White water bottle that says 'Silvera for Seniors' is a sipper style 500 ml bottle and is on a metal bottle cage that is located in the vertical rod of the bike just above the front gear chain\r\n\r\nAccessories:\r\n\r\nLock: A black coiled cable lock is attached around the frame, securing the bike when parked.\r\nGreen Bag: A small green bag is mounted on the handlebar stem, possibly used for small items or tools.\r\nReflectors: There are red rear reflectors and front-mounted white reflectors for visibility.\r\nBar Code: The bike features a barcode sticker on the frame near the handlebar with the number \"70410 01847.\"\r\n\r\nDistinctive Marks: The handlebar stem has visible rust and slight wear, while the grips show signs of extended use.",
